observations.recommendation:
4.15	We recommended and the LCE agreed to instruct the:
Municipal Engineer to carry out sufficient detailed engineering activities and ensure that the road right of way issues and similar problems are resolved prior to procurement of infrastructure projects;
Concerned contractors to rectify immediately the deficiencies noted on the above-mentioned projects to conform with the approved program of works without prejudice to taking appropriate actions against the contractors who refused to effect the required corrections.

We recommended  that the LCE instruct the 
BAC to submit the documentary evidences required under the Revised IRR to support the payments for audit purposes; 
Municipal Engineer office to (i) explain why they should not be held liable for the erroneous computations of ABC which resulted in the awarding of contract to an unqualified bidder; and (ii) henceforth ensure that computation of Approved Budget for the Contract (ABC) was in accordance with regulations.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

a)	 mobilize additional competent personnel from the Accounting Office, Property Section and create an inventory committee to facilitate the completion of physical count of all PPE items;

b)	strengthen the controls on the handling and recording procedures for PPE by performing a periodic reconciliation of accounting records with the property and actual inventory results;

c)	complete the data in the Property Cards and maintain an updated, complete files of AREs which shall be renewed every three years.

d)	investigate the causes for the missing/unaccounted PPE items including those not found on site and identify and the persons deemed liable therefor so that appropriate remedial measures could be taken before it is too late;

e)	instruct the Property Officer to prepare a complete Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) and request for inspection of the said unserviceable property as an initial step for the  disposal of said properties; and

f)	direct the disposal committee to adopt appropriate action for  the prompt disposal of all unserviceable properties in accordance with Section 79 of PD No. 1445, to prevent further deterioration and decline in value of the said assets.
